    "We provide the model with the text source and coding categories only and give it an instruction that it should be acting as \"...a research assistant\" (see Appendix B for details).",
    "We do not change other default parameters.",
    "Step 5: Performance evaluation",
    "The performance of text mining methods that use manually coded data as input should not be evaluated against the same data used when the model was built (or fine-tuned).",
    "Figure 2 summarizes our evaluation procedure: After selecting the sample of texts and coding it manually (Fig. 2a), we designate a randomly selected portion of this sample (80%) as the \"training\" set that will be used to build or fine-tune our models."
